ODM leader Raila Odinga and Deputy President William Ruto will on Saturday take their presidential vote hunt campaigns to the Mt Kenya region. Raila will take the Azimio la Umoja gospel to Murang'a county where he is scheduled to hold a mega rally at Ihura stadium. He will be accompanied by a host of other leaders allied the Azimio la Umoja movement from the Mt Kenya region. Raila has been on a charm offensive of Central Kenya, a region that has not supported him in the previous four elections. Deputy President William Ruto will also be in Kirinyaga county where he will popularise his party and presidential bid. The DP will hold a rally at Thiba Grounds in the county of Kirinyaga alongside his Kenya Kwanza coalition counterparts; Moses Wetangula and Musalia Mudavadi. This will be the trio's third mega rally as a team in just one week. Ruto will be accompanied by elected and aspiring leaders allied to UDA, ANC and Ford Kenya parties. On Friday, Raila attended the funeral of Nyeri Deputy Governor Caroline Karugu's mother and later addressed residents of Nyeri town. Ruto on the other hand, campaigned in Western counties of Bungoma and Kakamega.